reviewText: Part 1 of this two disc biography was on VHS, but I could never find the second part.  It was a real treat to finally find it and add it to my library.
This is a great companion for the Early Years DVD I enjoyed it immensly I Duke collection would not be complete without this one too.
This was totally better than I could have ever believed.  I thought that I had seen all there was about John Wayne, but this just added to it in the best way possible.

A couple of years ago I assemled a number of Wayne-Film Trailors and put them on a DVD. This DVD reminds me a lot of what I did then. Nothing new
for a fan,
Bought as a gift. Book was in excellent condition and will be prized by the recipient.

I purchased both this and the Early Years DVD....and they are a waste.  Mostly this is a strung together collection of very poor quality trailers of the movies Duke made during this period with some commercials thrown in....if you are a completist collector....ONLY
It was an o.k. movie not one of my favorites. I have seen many of his movies that have been a lot better.
love it well done lots of info
I collect John Wayne movies. I added this one to my collections.

The John Wayne The Later Years was very accurate in telling the story of the Duke's years from 1953-1976 which was his last film - It also said of his addiction to 4 packs a day of smoking cigarettes very heavily during his last years - This is what telling a story about a real American is all about - I have the Early Years of this, and everything that is and was said is true -  John Wayne made 142 filoms during his career, and personally, I own 106 of them, mostly taped from TV, but, I am a real John Wayne fan, as well as many members of my family are - Anybody and everybody, who is a real John Wayne fan, should get and have The John Wayne story, The Early Years and the Later Years both either on VHS or DVD.
well Ill tell ya baby sister..... he will always be alive in this secular world.  the Duke!  what a model we all should follow.

If you're a John Wayne fan .. this is a MUST!  Just love John Wayne... and this is a DVD you just can't find in the stores.  Any collector would welcome this -- The John Wayne Story -  The Later Years.  Well worth getting and wonderful addition to your collection!
